<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.92/493</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                                (<hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>) <hi rend="italic">of a
                                Conversation With the British Chargé</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Butler</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-30">January 30, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In regard to the fact that Japan is undertaking to mediate between the
                            French (Indochina) and Thailand: Mr. Butler expressed the opinion that
                            the British and the American Governments ought to signify to the
                            Japanese Government that we continue to have an interest in the
                            matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>